Visium Fund Manager, Others Arrested On Fraud Charges



        By Stewart Bishop



					Law360, New York (June 15, 2016,  4:12 PM EDT) -- Current and former portfolio managers for health care-focused hedge fund company Visium Asset Management LP on Wednesday were arrested on securities fraud charges for a pair of purported schemes to trade on inside government information and to falsely inflate one fund’s value.Sanjay Valvani, 44, is accused of conspiring with a consultant and former senior U.S. Food and Drug Administration official to obtain nonpublic information from the agency about pending generic drug applications, which netted at least $25 million in trading profits. Valvani also passed on...
				
