Visium Liquidates Fund, Sells Another to AllianceBernstein
Firm is at the center of an insider-trading scandal

 






By

Rob Copeland and 
              

Rob Copeland
The Wall Street Journal
BiographyRob Copeland
@realrobcopeland
rob.copeland@wsj.com



Sarah Krouse


Sarah Krouse
The Wall Street Journal
BiographySarah Krouse
@bysarahkrouse
sarah.krouse@wsj.com




  Updated June 17, 2016 7:29 p.m. ET





Hedge-fund firm Visium Asset Management LP will liquidate its flagship fund and sell another to a competitor, a fast end for the firm at the center of a new insider-trading case. The firm’s wind down comes just two days after federal prosecutors unveiled charges against current and former Visium portfolio managers for allegedly trading on confidential government information about generic-drug approvals. “Given the uncertainty...
  


